function rA(e, t, r) {
    let {reference: n, floating: a} = e;
    const s = Os(t)
      , o = Vj(t)
      , l = Uj(o)
      , c = Pa(t)
      , u = s === "y"
      , f = n.x + n.width / 2 - a.width / 2
      , d = n.y + n.height / 2 - a.height / 2
      , h = n[l] / 2 - a[l] / 2;
    let g;
    switch (c) {
    case "top":
        g = {
            x: f,
            y: n.y - a.height
        };
        break;
    case "bottom":
        g = {
            x: f,
            y: n.y + n.height
        };
        break;
    case "right":
        g = {
            x: n.x + n.width,
            y: d
        };
        break;
    case "left":
        g = {
            x: n.x - a.width,
            y: d
        };
        break;
    default:
        g = {
            x: n.x,
            y: n.y
        }
    }
    switch (su(t)) {
    case "start":
        g[o] -= h * (r && u ? -1 : 1);
        break;
    case "end":
        g[o] += h * (r && u ? -1 : 1);
        break
    }
    return g
}

function cW(e, t) {
    const r = Math.abs(t.top - e.y)
      , n = Math.abs(t.bottom - e.y)
      , a = Math.abs(t.right - e.x)
      , s = Math.abs(t.left - e.x);
    switch (Math.min(r, n, a, s)) {
    case s:
        return "left";
    case a:
        return "right";
    case r:
        return "top";
    case n:
        return "bottom";
    default:
        throw new Error("unreachable")
    }
}
function uW(e, t, r=5) {
    const n = [];
    switch (t) {
    case "top":
        n.push({
            x: e.x - r,

            x: e.x + r,
            y: e.y + r
        });
        break;
    case "bottom":
        n.push({
            x: e.x - r,
            y: e.y - r
        }, {
            x: e.x + r,
            y: e.y - r
        });
        break;
    case "left":
        n.push({
            x: e.x + r,
            y: e.y - r
        }, {
            x: e.x + r,
            y: e.y + r
        });

        n.push({
            x: e.x - r,
            y: e.y - r
        }, {
            x: e.x - r,
            y: e.y + r
        });
        break
    }
    return n
}

function IG({children: e}) {
    const [t,r] = p.useState(null)
      , [n,a] = p.useState(null)
      , [s,o] = p.useState(!0)
      , l = p.useCallback(h => {
        r(h),
        yl(h)
    }
    , [])
      , c = p.useCallback(h => {
        r(h),
        yl(h)
    }
    , [])
      , u = p.useCallback(async () => {
        try {
            await fetch("/api/auth/logout", {
                method: "POST",
                credentials: "include"
            })
        } catch (h) {
            console.error("Logout API call failed:", h)
        } finally {
            r(null),
            yl(null),
            a(null)
        }
    }
    , [])
      , f = p.useCallback(async () => {
        try {
            const h = await fetch("/api/auth/refresh", {
                method: "POST",
                credentials: "include"
            });
            if (!h.ok)
                return console.log("[AUTH] Token refresh failed:", h.status),
                null;
            const g = await h.json();
            return g.accessToken ? (r(g.accessToken),
            yl(g.accessToken),
            console.log("[AUTH] Access token refreshed successfully"),
            g.accessToken) : null
        } catch (h) {
            return console.error("[AUTH] Error refreshing token:", h),
            null
        }
    }
    , []);
    p.useEffect( () => (RC(f),
    DC(u),
    () => {
        RC(null),
        DC(null)
    }
    ), [f, u]),
    p.useCallback( () => FB(), []),
    p.useEffect( () => {
        (async () => {
            try {
                console.log("[AUTH] Initializing auth - attempting to refresh token");
                const g = window.location.hash
                  , v = new URLSearchParams(window.location.search);
                if (g.includes("token=")) {
                    const b = g.match(/token=([^&]+)/);
                    if (b && b[1]) {
                        const y = b[1];
                        console.log("[AUTH] Found OAuth token in URL fragment"),
                        r(y),
                        yl(y),
                        window.location.hash = "",
                        v.delete("login");
                        const x = v.toString()
                          , w = window.location.pathname + (x ? `?${x}` : "");
                        window.history.replaceState({}, "", w);
                        const S = await fetch("/api/auth/user", {
                            headers: {
                                Authorization: `Bearer ${y}`
                            },
                            credentials: "include"
                        });
                        if (S.ok) {
                            const j = await S.json();
                            a(j),
                            console.log("[AUTH] OAuth login successful - user data loaded"),
                            o(!1);
                            return
                        }
                    }
                }
                const m = await f();
                if (m) {
                    console.log("[AUTH] Token obtained - fetching user data");
                    const b = await fetch("/api/auth/user", {
                        headers: {
                            Authorization: `Bearer ${m}`
                        },
                        credentials: "include"
                    });
                    if (b.ok) {
                        const y = await b.json();
                        a(y),
                        console.log("[AUTH] User data loaded successfully")
                    } else
                        console.log("[AUTH] Failed to fetch user data:", b.status),
                        r(null),
                        a(null)
                } else
                    console.log("[AUTH] No valid refresh token - user not authenticated"),
                    a(null)
            } catch (g) {
                console.error("[AUTH] Error initializing auth:", g),
                r(null),
                a(null)
            } finally {
                o(!1)
            }
        }
        )()
    }
    , []);
    const d = {
        accessToken: t,
        setAccessToken: l,
        login: c,
        logout: u,
        refreshAccessToken: f,
        isAuthenticated: !!t && !!n,
        user: n,
        isLoading: s,
        setUser: a,
        setIsLoading: o
    };
    return i.jsx(y$.Provider, {
        value: d,
        children: e
    })
}
function nr() {
    const e = p.useContext(y$);
    if (e === void 0)
        throw new Error("useAuth must be used within an AuthProvider");
    return e
}
function $G() {
    const [e,t] = p.useState("light");
    p.useEffect( () => {
        const n = localStorage.getItem("theme")
          , a = window.matchMedia("(prefers-color-scheme: dark)").matches
          , s = n || (a ? "dark" : "light");
        t(s),
        document.documentElement.classList.toggle("dark", s === "dark")
    }
    , []);
    const r = () => {
        const n = e === "light" ? "dark" : "light";
        t(n),
        localStorage.setItem("theme", n),
        document.documentElement.classList.toggle("dark", n === "dark")
    }
    ;
    return i.jsx(G, {
        variant: "ghost",
        size: "icon",
        onClick: r,
        "data-testid": "button-theme-toggle",
        "aria-label": "Toggle theme",
        children: e === "light" ? i.jsx(t9, {
            className: "h-5 w-5"
        }) : i.jsx(s9, {
            className: "h-5 w-5"
        })
    })
}

        }, r.attr, n, o, {
            className: c,
            style: Ip(Ip({
                color: e.color || r.color
            }, r.style), e.style),
            height: l,
            width: l,
            xmlns: "http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
        }), s && V.createElement("title", null, s), e.children)
    }
    ;
    return SA !== void 0 ? V.createElement(SA.Consumer, null, r => t(r)) : t(s5)
}

function AA(e) {
    try {
        let t = e.trim();
        if (!t)
            return {
                success: !1,
                error: "Empty URL"
            };
        t.startsWith("//") ? t = `https:${t}` : !t.startsWith("http://") && !t.startsWith("https://") && (t = `https://${t}`);
        const r = new URL(t);
        if (!r.hostname.includes("vimeo.com"))
            return {
                success: !1,
                error: "Not a Vimeo URL"
            };
        let n;
        if (r.hostname === "player.vimeo.com")
            n = r;
        else {
            let a = null;
            const s = r.pathname
              , o = s.match(/\/video\/(\d+)/);
            if (o)
                a = o[1];
            else if (s.match(/\/videos\/(\d+)/))
                a = s.match(/\/videos\/(\d+)/)[1];
            else if (s.match(/^\/\d+$/))
                a = s.slice(1);
            else {
                const l = s.match(/\d+/g);
                l && l.length > 0 && (a = l[l.length - 1])
            }
            if (!a)
                return {
                    success: !1,
                    error: "Could not extract video ID from URL"
                };
            n = new URL(`https://player.vimeo.com/video/${a}`),
            r.searchParams.forEach( (l, c) => {
                n.searchParams.set(c, l)
            }
            )
        }
        return n.searchParams.set("background", "1"),
        n.searchParams.set("autoplay", "1"),
        n.searchParams.set("loop", "1"),
        n.searchParams.set("autopause", "0"),
        n.searchParams.set("muted", "1"),
        {
            success: !0,
            url: n.toString()
        }
    } catch (t) {
        return {
            success: !1,
            error: t instanceof Error ? t.message : "Unknown error"
        }
    }
}

                return s.url;
            console.error("Vimeo URL normalization failed:", s.error)
        }
        return null
    }

function _H() {
    const [,e] = Yo()
      , {toast: t} = ft()
      , {login: r, setUser: n} = nr()
      , [a,s] = p.useState(!1)
      , [o,l] = p.useState({
        email: "",
        password: ""
    })
      , c = async f => {
        f.preventDefault(),
        s(!0);
        try {
            const d = await fetch("/api/auth/login", {
                method: "POST",
                headers: {
                    "Content-Type": "application/json"
                },
                credentials: "include",
                body: JSON.stringify(o)
            })
              , h = await d.json();
            if (!d.ok)
                throw new Error(h.error || "Login failed");
            if (h.accessToken) {
                r(h.accessToken);
                const g = await fetch("/api/auth/user", {
                    headers: {
                        Authorization: `Bearer ${h.accessToken}`
                    },
                    credentials: "include"
                });
                if (g.ok) {
                    const v = await g.json();
                    n(v)
                }
            }
            t({
                title: "Welcome back!",
                description: "You have successfully logged in."
            }),
            e("/")
        } catch (d) {
            console.error("Login error:", d),
            t({
                title: "Login failed",
                description: d.message || "Invalid email or password. Please try again.",
                variant: "destructive"
            }),
            s(!1)
        }
    }
      , u = () => {
        window.location.href = "/auth/google"
    }
    ;
    return i.jsx("div", {
        className: "min-h-screen flex items-center justify-center bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-900 via-blue-900 to-black p-4",
        children: i.jsxs("div", {

                className: "flex flex-col items-center mb-8",

                        className: "h-8 w-8 text-purple-400"
                    }), i.jsx("h1", {
                        className: "text-3xl font-bold bg-gradient-to-r from-purple-400 to-blue-400 bg-clip-text text-transparent",
                        children: "Artivio AI"

                })]
            }), i.jsxs(H, {
                children: [i.jsxs(te, {
                    children: [i.jsx(re, {
                        children: "Sign In"
                    }), i.jsx(ge, {
                        children: "Enter your credentials to access your account"
                    })]
                }), i.jsxs(X, {
                    children: [i.jsxs("form", {
                        onSubmit: c,
                        className: "space-y-4",
                        children: [i.jsxs("div", {
                            className: "space-y-2",
                            children: [i.jsx(K, {
                                htmlFor: "email",
                                children: "Email"
                            }), i.jsx(je, {
                                id: "email",
                                type: "email",

                                value: o.email,
                                onChange: f => l({
                                    ...o,
                                    email: f.target.value
                                }),
                                required: !0,
                                disabled: a,
                                "data-testid": "input-email"
                            })]

                                htmlFor: "password",
                                children: "Password"
                            }), i.jsx(je, {

                            })]

function MH() {
    const [,e] = Yo()
      , {toast: t} = ft()
      , {login: r, setUser: n} = nr()
      , [a,s] = p.useState(!1)
      , [o,l] = p.useState({
        email: "",
        password: "",
        confirmPassword: "",
        name: ""
    })
      , c = async f => {
        if (f.preventDefault(),
        o.password !== o.confirmPassword) {
            t({
                title: "Password mismatch",
                description: "Passwords do not match. Please try again.",
                variant: "destructive"
            });
            return
        }
        if (o.password.length < 8) {
            t({
                title: "Weak password",
                description: "Password must be at least 8 characters long.",
                variant: "destructive"
            });
            return
        }
        s(!0);
        try {
            const d = await fetch("/api/auth/register", {
                method: "POST",
                headers: {
                    "Content-Type": "application/json"
                },
                credentials: "include",
                body: JSON.stringify({
                    email: o.email,
                    password: o.password,
                    name: o.name
                })
            })
              , h = await d.json();
            if (!d.ok)
                throw new Error(h.error || "Registration failed");
            if (h.accessToken) {
                r(h.accessToken);
                const g = await fetch("/api/auth/user", {
                    headers: {
                        Authorization: `Bearer ${h.accessToken}`
                    },
                    credentials: "include"
                });
                if (g.ok) {
                    const v = await g.json();
                    n(v)
                }
            }
            t({
                title: "Account created!",
                description: "Welcome to Artivio AI. Please select a subscription plan to get started."
            }),
            e("/pricing")
        } catch (d) {
            console.error("Registration error:", d),
            t({
                title: "Registration failed",
                description: d.message || "Failed to create account. Please try again.",
                variant: "destructive"
            }),
            s(!1)
        }
    }
      , u = () => {
        window.location.href = "/auth/google"
    }
    ;
    return i.jsx("div", {
        className: "min-h-screen flex items-center justify-center bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-900 via-blue-900 to-black p-4",
        children: i.jsxs("div", {
            className: "w-full max-w-md",
            children: [i.jsxs("div", {
                className: "flex flex-col items-center mb-8",

                    className: "flex items-center gap-2 mb-2",
                    children: [i.jsx(ot, {
                        className: "h-8 w-8 text-purple-400"
                    }), i.jsx("h1", {
                        className: "text-3xl font-bold bg-gradient-to-r from-purple-400 to-blue-400 bg-clip-text text-transparent",

                    })]
                }), i.jsx("p", {
                    className: "text-gray-400 text-center",

                })]
            }), i.jsxs(H, {
                children: [i.jsxs(te, {
                    children: [i.jsx(re, {
                        children: "Create Account"
                    }), i.jsx(ge, {
                        children: "Sign up to get started with your free trial"
                    })]
                }), i.jsxs(X, {
                    children: [i.jsxs("form", {
                        onSubmit: c,
                        className: "space-y-4",
                        children: [i.jsxs("div", {
                            className: "space-y-2",
                            children: [i.jsx(K, {
                                htmlFor: "name",
                                children: "Full Name"
                            }), i.jsx(je, {
                                id: "name",
                                type: "text",
                                placeholder: "John Doe",
                                value: o.name,
                                onChange: f => l({
                                    ...o,
                                    name: f.target.value
                                }),
                                required: !0,
                                disabled: a,
                                "data-testid": "input-name"
                            })]
                        }), i.jsxs("div", {

function IH() {
    const [e,t] = p.useState(null)
      , [r,n] = p.useState(!1)
      , {toast: a} = ft()
      , {user: s} = nr()
      , {data: o, isLoading: l} = Qe({
        queryKey: ["/api/plans"]
    })
      , {data: c, isLoading: u, isError: f} = Qe({
        queryKey: ["/api/subscriptions/current"],
        queryFn: async () => {
            const v = await Kd("/api/subscriptions/current");
            if (!v.ok)
                throw new Error("Failed to fetch subscription");
            return v.json()
        }
        ,
        enabled: !!s,
        retry: !1,
        refetchOnWindowFocus: !1,
        gcTime: 0
    })
      , d = c == null ? void 0 : c.planId
      , h = (o == null ? void 0 : o.map(v => ({
        ...v,
        popular: v.name === "starter"
    }))) || []
      , g = async v => {
        if (v.id === d) {
            a({
                title: "Already subscribed",
                description: "You are already on this plan.",
                variant: "default"
            });
            return
        }
        t(v.name),
        n(!0);
        try {
            if (v.price === 0) {
                if (!(await fetch("/api/public/plan-selection", {
                    method: "POST",
                    headers: {
                        "Content-Type": "application/json"
                    },
                    credentials: "include",
                    body: JSON.stringify({
                        planName: v.name
                    })
                })).ok)
                    throw new Error("Failed to store plan selection");
                window.location.href = "/register"
            } else {
                const m = await Kd("/api/billing/checkout", {
                    method: "POST",
                    headers: {
                        "Content-Type": "application/json"
                    },
                    credentials: "include",
                    body: JSON.stringify({
                        planId: v.id
                    })
                })
                  , b = await m.json();
                if (!m.ok)
                    throw new Error(b.error || "Failed to create checkout session");
                if (b.url)
                    window.location.href = b.url;
                else
                    throw new Error("No checkout URL returned")
            }
        } catch (m) {
            console.error("Error selecting plan:", m),
            a({
                title: "Error",
                description: m.message || "Failed to select plan. Please try again.",
                variant: "destructive"
            }),
            n(!1)
        }
    }
    ;
    return i.jsxs("div", {
        className: "min-h-screen bg-background",
        children: [i.jsx("header", {
            className: "border-b",
            children: i.jsx("div", {
                className: "container mx-auto px-4 py-4",
                children: i.jsx("div", {
                    className: "flex items-center justify-between",
                    children: i.jsx("h1", {
                        className: "text-2xl font-bold bg-gradient-to-r from-primary to-accent bg-clip-text text-transparent",
                        children: "Artivio AI"
                    })
                })
            })
        }), i.jsxs("section", {
            className: "container mx-auto px-4 py-16",
            children: [i.jsxs("div", {
                className: "text-center mb-12",
                children: [i.jsx("h1", {
                    className: "text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-4",
                    children: "Choose Your Plan"
                }), i.jsx("p", {
                    className: "text-xl text-muted-foreground max-w-2xl mx-auto",
                    children: "Select the perfect plan for your AI content creation needs. Start creating amazing videos, images, and music today."
                })]
            }), l ? i.jsx("div", {
                className: "flex justify-center items-center py-16",
                children: i.jsx(we, {
                    className: "h-8 w-8 animate-spin text-primary",
                    "data-testid": "loader-plans"
                })
            }) : i.jsxs(i.Fragment, {
                children: [i.jsx("div", {
                    className: "grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 max-w-6xl mx-auto",
                    children: h.map(v => {
                        const m = Array.isArray(v.features) ? v.features : []
                          , b = v.billingPeriod === "trial"
                          , y = s && !u && !f && v.id === d;
                        return i.jsxs(H, {
                            className: `relative hover-elevate ${v.popular ? "border-primary shadow-lg" : ""} ${e === v.name ? "ring-2 ring-primary" : ""} ${y ? "opacity-70" : ""}`,
                            "data-testid": `card-plan-${v.name}`,
                            children: [v.popular && i.jsx("div", {
                                className: "absolute -top-4 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2",
                                children: i.jsx("span", {
                                    className: "bg-primary text-primary-foreground px-4 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold",
                                    children: "Most Popular"
                                })
                            }), i.jsxs(te, {
                                className: "text-center pt-8",
                                children: [i.jsx(re, {
                                    className: "text-2xl mb-2",
                                    children: v.displayName
                                }), i.jsx(ge, {
                                    children: v.description
                                }), i.jsxs("div", {
                                    className: "mt-4",
                                    children: [i.jsxs("span", {
                                        className: "text-4xl font-bold",
                                        children: ["$", ( () => {
                                            const x = v.price / 100;
                                            return x % 1 === 0 ? x.toFixed(0) : x.toFixed(2)
                                        }
                                        )()]
                                    }), i.jsx("span", {

                                    })]
                                }), i.jsxs("p", {

                                })]
                            }), i.jsx(X, {
                                children: i.jsx("ul", {
                                    className: "space-y-3",

                                        }), i.jsx("span", {

                                            children: x
                                        })]
                                    }, w))
                                })
                            }), i.jsx(Yn, {
                                children: i.jsx(G, {
                                    onClick: () => g(v),

                                        }), v.price === 0 ? "Starting Trial..." : "Processing..."]

                                })
                            })]

                        })]
                    }), i.jsx(H, {

                                        }), i.jsx("span", {

                                        })]

                                        })]
                                    }), i.jsxs("li", {
                                        className: "flex items-start gap-2",
                                        children: [i.jsx(Qt, {

                                        }), i.jsx("span", {
                                            className: "text-sm",

                                        })]
                                    }), i.jsxs("li", {

                                        children: [i.jsx(Qt, {

function FH(e, t) {
    return `${Math.round(e / t * 100)}%`
}
function g5(e, t) {
    return e == null ? "indeterminate" : e === t ? "complete" : "loading"
}
function $p(e) {
    return typeof e == "number"
}
function OA(e) {
    return $p(e) && !isNaN(e) && e > 0
}
function kA(e, t) {
    return $p(e) && !isNaN(e) && e <= t && e >= 0
}
function zH(e, t) {
    return `Invalid prop \`max\` of value \`${e}\` supplied to \`${t}\`. Only numbers greater than 0 are valid max values. Defaulting to \`${_2}\`.`
}
function BH(e, t) {
    return `Invalid prop \`value\` of value \`${e}\` supplied to \`${t}\`. The \`value\` prop must be:
  - a positive number
  - less than the value passed to \`max\` (or ${_2} if no \`max\` prop is set)
  - \`null\` or \`undefined\` if the progress is indeterminate.

}

function Fu(e) {
    return (t, r={}) => {
        const n = r.width
          , a = n && e.matchPatterns[n] || e.matchPatterns[e.defaultMatchWidth]
          , s = t.match(a);
        if (!s)
            return null;
        const o = s[0]
          , l = n && e.parsePatterns[n] || e.parsePatterns[e.defaultParseWidth]
          , c = Array.isArray(l) ? KK(l, d => d.test(o)) : HK(l, d => d.test(o));
        let u;
        u = e.valueCallback ? e.valueCallback(c) : c,
        u = r.valueCallback ? r.valueCallback(u) : u;
        const f = t.slice(o.length);
        return {
            value: u,
            rest: f
        }
    }
}
function HK(e, t) {
    for (const r in e)
        if (Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call(e, r) && t(e[r]))

function KK(e, t) {

            return r

function YK(e) {

        const n = t.match(e.matchPattern);
        if (!n)
            return null;
        const a = n[0]
          , s = t.match(e.parsePattern);
        if (!s)
            return null;
        let o = e.valueCallback ? e.valueCallback(s[0]) : s[0];
        o = r.valueCallback ? r.valueCallback(o) : o;
        const l = t.slice(a.length);
        return {
            value: o,
            rest: l
        }
    }
}

const qa = {
    y(e, t) {
        const r = e.getFullYear()
          , n = r > 0 ? r : 1 - r;
        return xt(t === "yy" ? n % 100 : n, t.length)
    },
    M(e, t) {
        const r = e.getMonth();
        return t === "M" ? String(r + 1) : xt(r + 1, 2)
    },
    d(e, t) {
        return xt(e.getDate(), t.length)
    },
    a(e, t) {
        const r = e.getHours() / 12 >= 1 ? "pm" : "am";
        switch (t) {
        case "a":
        case "aa":
            return r.toUpperCase();
        case "aaa":
            return r;
        case "aaaaa":
            return r[0];
        case "aaaa":
        default:
            return r === "am" ? "a.m." : "p.m."
        }
    },
    h(e, t) {
        return xt(e.getHours() % 12 || 12, t.length)
    },
    H(e, t) {
        return xt(e.getHours(), t.length)
    },
    m(e, t) {
        return xt(e.getMinutes(), t.length)
    },
    s(e, t) {
        return xt(e.getSeconds(), t.length)

            });
        case "MMMMM":
            return r.month(n, {
                width: "narrow",
                context: "formatting"
            });
        case "MMMM":
        default:

                width: "wide",
                context: "formatting"
            })
        }
    },
    L: function(e, t, r) {

        case "LL":

        case "i":

        case "ii":

        case "io":
            return r.ordinalNumber(a, {

            });

    a: function(e, t, r) {

    b: function(e, t, r) {

        t) {
        case "b":

            return r.dayPeriod(a, {
                width: "abbreviated",
                context: "formatting"

        t) {

            })
        }
    },
    h: function(e, t, r) {

            return n === 0 && (n = 12),
            r.ordinalNumber(n, {
                unit: "hour"
            })
        }

    H: function(e, t, r) {

    },

    k: function(e, t, r) {

        t === "ko" ? r.ordinalNumber(n, {

        }) : qa.m(e, t)
    },

        }) : qa.s(e, t)
    },
    S: function(e, t) {
        return qa.S(e, t)
    },
    X: function(e, t, r) {
        const n = e.getTimezoneOffset();
        if (n === 0)
            return "Z";
        switch (t) {
        case "X":
            return $A(n);
        case "XXXX":
        case "XX":
            return Js(n);
        case "XXXXX":
        case "XXX":
        default:
            return Js(n, ":")
        }
    },
    x: function(e, t, r) {
        const n = e.getTimezoneOffset();
        switch (t) {
        case "x":
            return $A(n);
        case "xxxx":
        case "xx":
            return Js(n);
        case "xxxxx":
        case "xxx":
        default:
            return Js(n, ":")
        }
    },
    O: function(e, t, r) {
        const n = e.getTimezoneOffset();
        switch (t) {
        case "O":
        case "OO":
        case "OOO":
            return "GMT" + IA(n, ":");
        case "OOOO":
        default:
            return "GMT" + Js(n, ":")
        }
    },
    z: function(e, t, r) {
        const n = e.getTimezoneOffset();
        switch (t) {
        case "z":
        case "zz":
        case "zzz":
            return "GMT" + IA(n, ":");
        case "zzzz":
        default:
            return "GMT" + Js(n, ":")
        }
    },
    t: function(e, t, r) {
        const n = Math.trunc(e.getTime() / 1e3);
        return xt(n, t.length)
    },
    T: function(e, t, r) {
        const n = e.getTime();
        return xt(n, t.length)
    }
};
function IA(e, t="") {
    const r = e > 0 ? "-" : "+"
      , n = Math.abs(e)
      , a = Math.trunc(n / 60)
      , s = n % 60;
    return s === 0 ? r + String(a) : r + String(a) + t + xt(s, 2)
}
function $A(e, t) {
    return e % 60 === 0 ? (e > 0 ? "-" : "+") + xt(Math.abs(e) / 60, 2) : Js(e, t)
}
function Js(e, t="") {
    const r = e > 0 ? "-" : "+"
      , n = Math.abs(e)
      , a = xt(Math.trunc(n / 60), 2)
      , s = xt(n % 60, 2);
    return r + a + t + s
}
const RA = (e, t) => {
    switch (e) {
    case "P":
        return t.date({
            width: "short"
        });
    case "PP":
        return t.date({
            width: "medium"
        });
    case "PPP":
        return t.date({
            width: "long"
        });
    case "PPPP":
    default:
        return t.date({
            width: "full"
        })
    }
}
  , t3 = (e, t) => {
    switch (e) {
    case "p":
        return t.time({
            width: "short"
        });
    case "pp":
        return t.time({
            width: "medium"
        });
    case "ppp":
        return t.time({
            width: "long"
        });
    case "pppp":
    default:
        return t.time({
            width: "full"
        })
    }
}
  , hY = (e, t) => {
    const r = e.match(/(P+)(p+)?/) || []
      , n = r[1]
      , a = r[2];
    if (!a)
        return RA(e, t);
    let s;
    switch (n) {
    case "P":
        s = t.dateTime({
            width: "short"
        });
        break;
    case "PP":
        s = t.dateTime({
            width: "medium"
        });
        break;
    case "PPP":
        s = t.dateTime({
            width: "long"
        });
        break;
    case "PPPP":
    default:
        s = t.dateTime({
            width: "full"
        });
        break
    }
    return s.replace("{{date}}", RA(n, t)).replace("{{time}}", t3(a, t))
}
  , mY = {
    p: t3,
    P: hY
}
  , pY = /^D+$/
  , gY = /^Y+$/
  , vY = ["D", "DD", "YY", "YYYY"];
function xY(e) {
    return pY.test(e)
}
function yY(e) {
    return gY.test(e)
}
function bY(e, t, r) {
    const n = wY(e, t, r);
    if (console.warn(n),
    vY.includes(e))
        throw new RangeError(n)
}
function wY(e, t, r) {
    const n = e[0] === "Y" ? "years" : "days of the month";
    return `Use \`${e.toLowerCase()}\` instead of \`${e}\` (in \`${t}\`) for formatting ${n} to the input \`${r}\`; see: https://github.com/date-fns/date-fns/blob/master/docs/unicodeTokens.md`
}
const jY = /[yYQqMLwIdDecihHKkms]o|(\w)\1*|''|'(''|[^'])+('|$)|./g
  , NY = /P+p+|P+|p+|''|'(''|[^'])+('|$)|./g
  , SY = /^'([^]*?)'?$/
  , CY = /''/g
  , AY = /[a-zA-Z]/;
function zp(e, t, r) {
    var f, d, h, g;
    const n = gh()
      , a = n.locale ?? J5
      , s = n.firstWeekContainsDate ?? ((d = (f = n.locale) == null ? void 0 : f.options) == null ? void 0 : d.firstWeekContainsDate) ?? 1
      , o = n.weekStartsOn ?? ((g = (h = n.locale) == null ? void 0 : h.options) == null ? void 0 : g.weekStartsOn) ?? 0
      , l = Ct(e);
    if (!wK(l))
        throw new RangeError("Invalid time value");
    let c = t.match(NY).map(v => {
        const m = v[0];
        if (m === "p" || m === "P") {
            const b = mY[m];
            return b(v, a.formatLong)
        }
        return v
    }
    ).join("").match(jY).map(v => {
        if (v === "''")
            return {
                isToken: !1,
                value: "'"
            };
        const m = v[0];
        if (m === "'")
            return {
                isToken: !1,
                value: PY(v)
            };
        if (MA[m])
            return {
                isToken: !0,
                value: v
            };
        if (m.match(AY))
            throw new RangeError("Format string contains an unescaped latin alphabet character `" + m + "`");
        return {
            isToken: !1,
            value: v
        }
    }
    );
    a.localize.preprocessor && (c = a.localize.preprocessor(l, c));
    const u = {
        firstWeekContainsDate: s,
        weekStartsOn: o,
        locale: a
    };
    return c.map(v => {
        if (!v.isToken)
            return v.value;
        const m = v.value;
        (yY(m) || xY(m)) && bY(m, t, String(e));
        const b = MA[m[0]];
        return b(l, m, a.localize, u)
    }
    ).join("")
}
function PY(e) {
    const t = e.match(SY);
    return t ? t[1].replace(CY, "'") : e
}
function OY(e, t, r) {
    const n = gh()
      , a = (r == null ? void 0 : r.locale) ?? n.locale ?? J5
      , s = 2520
      , o = Km(e, t);
    if (isNaN(o))
        throw new RangeError("Invalid time value");
    const l = Object.assign({}, r, {
        addSuffix: r == null ? void 0 : r.addSuffix,
        comparison: o
    });
    let c, u;
    o > 0 ? (c = Ct(t),
    u = Ct(e)) : (c = Ct(e),
    u = Ct(t));
    const f = kK(u, c)
      , d = (Fp(u) - Fp(c)) / 1e3
      , h = Math.round((f - d) / 60);
    let g;
    if (h < 2)
        return r != null && r.includeSeconds ? f < 5 ? a.formatDistance("lessThanXSeconds", 5, l) : f < 10 ? a.formatDistance("lessThanXSeconds", 10, l) : f < 20 ? a.formatDistance("lessThanXSeconds", 20, l) : f < 40 ? a.formatDistance("halfAMinute", 0, l) : f < 60 ? a.formatDistance("lessThanXMinutes", 1, l) : a.formatDistance("xMinutes", 1, l) : h === 0 ? a.formatDistance("lessThanXMinutes", 1, l) : a.formatDistance("xMinutes", h, l);
    if (h < 45)
        return a.formatDistance("xMinutes", h, l);
    if (h < 90)
        return a.formatDistance("aboutXHours", 1, l);
    if (h < TA) {
        const v = Math.round(h / 60);
        return a.formatDistance("aboutXHours", v, l)
    } else {
        if (h < s)
            return a.formatDistance("xDays", 1, l);
        if (h < lm) {
            const v = Math.round(h / TA);
            return a.formatDistance("xDays", v, l)
        } else if (h < lm * 2)
            return g = Math.round(h / lm),
            a.formatDistance("aboutXMonths", g, l)
    }
    if (g = OK(u, c),
    g < 12) {
        const v = Math.round(h / lm);
        return a.formatDistance("xMonths", v, l)
    } else {
        const v = g % 12
          , m = Math.trunc(g / 12);
        return v < 3 ? a.formatDistance("aboutXYears", m, l) : v < 9 ? a.formatDistance("overXYears", m, l) : a.formatDistance("almostXYears", m + 1, l)
    }
}
function ga(e, t) {
    return OY(e, yK(e), t)
}
function kY() {

      , f = l.filter(x => x.status === "completed" || x.status === "failed").slice(0, 5);

        u.length === 0 && t ? r(!1) : u.length > 0 && !t && r(!0)
    }
    , [u.length, t]);

        mutationFn: async x => {

function EY() {
    const {toast: e} = ft()
      , [t,r] = p.useState(!0)
      , {data: n, isLoading: a, isError: s, error: o} = Qe({
        queryKey: ["/api/onboarding"],
        retry: 2,
        staleTime: 1e3 * 60 * 5
    })
      , l = Ge({
        mutationFn: async h => (await Le("PATCH", "/api/onboarding", h)).json(),
        onSuccess: () => {
            tt.invalidateQueries({
                queryKey: ["/api/onboarding"]
            })
        }
        ,
        onError: h => {
            e({
                title: "Error",
                description: "Failed to update onboarding progress",
                variant: "destructive"
            }),
            console.error("Onboarding update error:", h)
        }
    });
    if (a)
        return i.jsx(H, {
            className: "border-primary/20 bg-gradient-to-br from-primary/5 to-primary/10",
            children: i.jsx(te, {
                children: i.jsxs("div", {
                    className: "flex items-center gap-2",
                    children: [i.jsx(ot, {
                        className: "h-5 w-5 text-primary animate-pulse"
                    }), i.jsx(re, {
                        children: "Loading your progress..."
                    })]
                })
            })
        });
    if (s)
        return console.error("Onboarding fetch error:", o),
        i.jsx(H, {
            className: "border-destructive/20 bg-destructive/5",
            children: i.jsxs(te, {
                children: [i.jsxs("div", {
                    className: "flex items-center justify-between",
                    children: [i.jsxs("div", {
                        className: "flex items-center gap-2",
                        children: [i.jsx(ot, {
                            className: "h-5 w-5 text-destructive"
                        }), i.jsx(re, {
                            children: "Welcome to Artivio AI!"
                        })]
                    }), i.jsx(G, {
                        variant: "ghost",
                        size: "sm",
                        onClick: () => tt.invalidateQueries({
                            queryKey: ["/api/onboarding"]
                        }),
                        "data-testid": "button-onboarding-retry",
                        className: "h-8 gap-2",
                        children: "Retry"
                    })]
                }), i.jsx(ge, {
                    children: "Couldn't load your onboarding progress. Click retry or continue exploring."
                })]
            })
        });
    if (!n || n.dismissed)
        return null;
    const c = zu.filter(h => n[h.id]).length
      , u = c === zu.length
      , f = c / zu.length * 100
      , d = () => {
        l.mutate({
            dismissed: !0
        })
    }
    ;
    return i.jsxs(H, {
        className: "border-primary/20 bg-gradient-to-br from-primary/5 to-primary/10",
        children: [i.jsx(te, {
            className: "pb-3",
            children: i.jsxs("div", {
                className: "flex items-start justify-between gap-2",
                children: [i.jsxs("div", {
                    className: "flex-1",
                    children: [i.jsxs("div", {
                        className: "flex items-center gap-2",
                        children: [i.jsx(ot, {
                            className: "h-5 w-5 text-primary"
                        }), i.jsx(re, {
                            children: "Welcome to Artivio AI!"
                        }), u && i.jsxs(ke, {
                            variant: "default",
                            className: "ml-2",
                            children: [i.jsx(Qt, {
                                className: "h-3 w-3 mr-1"
                            }), "Complete"]
                        })]
                    }), i.jsx(ge, {
                        className: "mt-1",
                        children: u ? "You've completed the quickstart! Keep creating amazing content." : `Get started by completing these steps (${c}/${zu.length})`
                    })]
                }), i.jsxs("div", {
                    className: "flex items-center gap-1",
                    children: [!u && i.jsx(G, {
                        variant: "ghost",
                        size: "sm",
                        onClick: () => r(!t),
                        "data-testid": "button-onboarding-toggle",
                        className: "h-8 w-8 p-0",
                        children: i.jsx(Pi, {
                            className: `h-4 w-4 transition-transform ${t ? "rotate-90" : ""}`
                        })
                    }), i.jsx(G, {
                        variant: "ghost",
                        size: "sm",
                        onClick: d,
                        "data-testid": "button-onboarding-dismiss",
                        className: "h-8 w-8 p-0",
                        children: i.jsx(Cn, {
                            className: "h-4 w-4"
                        })
                    })]
                })]
            })
        }), t && i.jsxs(X, {
            className: "space-y-4 pt-0",
            children: [i.jsxs("div", {
                className: "space-y-2",
                children: [i.jsxs("div", {
                    className: "flex items-center justify-between text-sm",
                    children: [i.jsx("span", {
                        className: "text-muted-foreground",
                        children: "Your Progress"
                    }), i.jsxs("span", {
                        className: "font-medium",
                        children: [Math.round(f), "%"]
                    })]
                }), i.jsx(M2, {
                    value: f,
                    className: "h-2",
                    "data-testid": "progress-onboarding"
                })]
            }), i.jsx("div", {
                className: "grid gap-3",
                children: zu.map(h => {
                    const g = n[h.id]
                      , v = h.icon;
                    return i.jsx(et, {
                        href: h.link,
                        "data-testid": h.dataTestId,
                        children: i.jsxs("div", {
                            className: `
                      flex items-start gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border transition-all
                      ${g ? "bg-primary/5 border-primary/20" : "hover-elevate active-elevate-2 border-border cursor-pointer"}
                    `,
                            children: [i.jsx("div", {
                                className: `
                      flex items-center justify-center h-10 w-10 rounded-full flex-shrink-0
                      ${g ? "bg-primary text-primary-foreground" : "bg-muted"}
                    `,
                                children: g ? i.jsx(Qt, {
                                    className: "h-5 w-5"
                                }) : i.jsx(v, {
                                    className: "h-5 w-5"
                                })
                            }), i.jsxs("div", {
                                className: "flex-1 min-w-0",
                                children: [i.jsxs("div", {
                                    className: "flex items-center justify-between gap-2",
                                    children: [i.jsx("h4", {
                                        className: "font-medium",
                                        children: h.title
                                    }), g && i.jsx(ke, {
                                        variant: "outline",
                                        className: "bg-primary/10 border-primary/20",
                                        children: "Done"
                                    })]
                                }), i.jsx("p", {
                                    className: "text-sm text-muted-foreground mt-0.5",
                                    children: h.description
                                })]
                            }), !g && i.jsx(Pi, {
                                className: "h-5 w-5 text-muted-foreground flex-shrink-0 mt-2"
                            })]
                        })
                    }, h.id)
                }
                )
            }), u && i.jsx("div", {
                className: "pt-2 border-t",
                children: i.jsx("p", {
                    className: "text-sm text-center text-muted-foreground",
                    children: " Great job! You're all set. Feel free to dismiss this card."
                })
            })]
        })]
    })
}

function yh() {

    }
}

function wQ(e=[], t, r) {
    const n = [...e];
    return n[r] = t,
    n.sort( (a, s) => a - s)
}
function hR(e, t, r) {
    const s = 100 / (r - t) * (e - t);
    return rf(s, [0, 100])
}
function jQ(e, t) {
    return t > 2 ? `Value ${e + 1} of ${t}` : t === 2 ? ["Minimum", "Maximum"][e] : void 0
}
function NQ(e, t) {
    if (e.length === 1)
        return 0;
    const r = e.map(a => Math.abs(a - t))
      , n = Math.min(...r);
    return r.indexOf(n)
}
function SQ(e, t, r) {
    const n = e / 2
      , s = U2([0, 50], [0, n]);
    return (n - s(t) * r) * r
}
function CQ(e) {
    return e.slice(0, -1).map( (t, r) => e[r + 1] - t)
}
function AQ(e, t) {
    if (t > 0) {
        const r = CQ(e);
        return Math.min(...r) >= t
    }
    return !0
}
function U2(e, t) {
    return r => {
        if (e[0] === e[1] || t[0] === t[1])
            return t[0];
        const n = (t[1] - t[0]) / (e[1] - e[0]);
        return t[0] + n * (r - e[0])
    }
}

    return (String(e).split(".")[1] || "").length
}
function OQ(e, t) {
    const r = Math.pow(10, t);
    return Math.round(e * r) / r
}

const qQ = `Hello! I'm excited to help you create a high-quality voice clone. This script is designed to capture the full range of your voice, including different tones, emotions, and phonetic sounds.

Let's start with some everyday conversation. I love spending time outdoors, whether it's hiking in the mountains or relaxing at the beach. There's something magical about nature that helps me clear my mind and find inspiration. Technology has transformed how we live and work, connecting people across the globe in ways we never imagined possible.

Now, let's explore different emotions and tones. I'm absolutely thrilled when I discover something new! But sometimes, I feel a bit worried when things don't go as planned. It's important to stay calm and think things through carefully. Questions like "What should I do next?" or "How can I solve this problem?" help guide my decisions.

Here are some challenging phonetic combinations: The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog. She sells seashells by the seashore. How much wood would a woodchuck chuck if a woodchuck could chuck wood? Peter Piper picked a peck of pickled peppers.

Let's practice numbers and technical terms: The meeting is scheduled for 3:45 PM on February 15th, 2025. Our address is 1234 Oak Street, Apartment 567. The total came to $89.99, including tax. Technical specifications include 256 gigabytes of storage and 16 gigabytes of RAM.

Finally, let's vary the pitch and pace. Sometimes I speak quickly when I'm excited about something! Other times, I slow down to emphasize important points. I might whisper softly when sharing a secret, or project my voice clearly when making an announcement.

Thank you for taking the time to record this script. Your patience and clear pronunciation will help create an excellent voice clone!`;
function GQ() {
    const {toast: e} = ft()
      , {isAuthenticated: t, isLoading: r} = nr()
      , n = Is()
      , {getModelCost: a} = Ni()
      , [s,o] = p.useState("")
      , [l,c] = p.useState("")
      , [u,f] = p.useState([])
      , [d,h] = p.useState(!1)
      , [g,v] = p.useState(!1)
      , [m,b] = p.useState(!1)
      , [y,x] = p.useState(0)
      , [w,S] = p.useState(null)
      , [j,C] = p.useState(!1)
      , [O,_] = p.useState(!1)
      , T = p.useRef(null)
      , L = p.useRef([])
      , R = p.useRef(null)
      , B = p.useRef(null)
      , I = p.useRef(null);
    p.useEffect( () => {
        !r && !t && (e({
            title: "Unauthorized",
            description: "You are logged out. Logging in again...",
            variant: "destructive"
        }),
        setTimeout( () => {
            window.location.href = "/login"
        }
        , 500))
    }
    , [t, r, e]);
    const {data: A=[], isLoading: E} = Qe({
        queryKey: ["/api/voice-clones"],
        enabled: t
    })
      , M = Ge({
        mutationFn: async Z => await Le("POST", "/api/voice-clone", Z),
        onSuccess: () => {
            e({
                title: "Voice Cloned Successfully",
                description: "Your voice has been cloned and is ready to use!"
            }),
            n.invalidateQueries({
                queryKey: ["/api/voice-clones"]
            }),
            o(""),
            c(""),
            f([])
        }
        ,
        onError: Z => {
            if (bh(Z)) {
                e({
                    title: "Unauthorized",
                    description: "You are logged out. Logging in again...",
                    variant: "destructive"
                }),
                setTimeout( () => {
                    window.location.href = "/login"
                }
                , 500);
                return
            }
            e({
                title: "Cloning Failed",
                description: Z.message || "Failed to clone voice. Please try again.",
                variant: "destructive"
            })
        }
    })
      , P = Ge({
        mutationFn: async ({voiceId: Z, isActive: F}) => await Le("PATCH", `/api/voice-clones/${Z}/toggle`, {
            isActive: F
        }),
        onSuccess: () => {
            n.invalidateQueries({
                queryKey: ["/api/voice-clones"]
            })
        }
        ,
        onError: Z => {
            e({
                title: "Update Failed",
                description: Z.message || "Failed to update voice status.",
                variant: "destructive"
            })
        }
    })
      , N = Ge({
        mutationFn: async Z => await Le("DELETE", `/api/voice-clones/${Z}`),
        onSuccess: () => {
            e({
                title: "Voice Deleted",
                description: "Voice clone has been removed successfully."
            }),
            n.invalidateQueries({
                queryKey: ["/api/voice-clones"]
            })
        }
        ,
        onError: Z => {
            e({
                title: "Delete Failed",
                description: Z.message || "Failed to delete voice clone.",
                variant: "destructive"
            })
        }
    })
      , k = async Z => {
        const F = Z.target.files;
        if (!(!F || F.length === 0)) {
            if (u.length + F.length > 3) {
                e({
                    title: "Too Many Files",
                    description: "Maximum 3 audio files allowed.",
                    variant: "destructive"
                });
                return
            }
            h(!0);
            try {
                const Y = [];
                for (let W = 0; W < F.length; W++) {
                    const ee = F[W];
                    if (!ee.type.startsWith("audio/")) {
                        e({
                            title: "Invalid File Type",
                            description: `${ee.name} is not an audio file.`,
                            variant: "destructive"
                        });
                        continue
                    }
                    if (ee.size > 10 * 1024 * 1024) {
                        e({
                            title: "File Too Large",
                            description: `${ee.name} exceeds 10MB limit.`,
                            variant: "destructive"
                        });
                        continue
                    }
                    const se = await new Promise(ve => {
                        const Te = new FileReader;
                        Te.onload = () => ve(Te.result),
                        Te.readAsDataURL(ee)
                    }
                    );
                    Y.push(se)
                }
                f([...u, ...Y]),
                e({
                    title: "Files Uploaded",
                    description: `${Y.length} audio file(s) added.`
                })
            } catch {
                e({
                    title: "Upload Failed",
                    description: "Failed to process audio files.",
                    variant: "destructive"
                })
            } finally {
                h(!1)
            }
        }
    }
      , $ = () => {
        if (!s.trim()) {
            e({
                title: "Name Required",
                description: "Please enter a name for your voice clone.",
                variant: "destructive"
            });
            return
        }
        if (u.length === 0) {
            e({
                title: "Audio Required",
                description: "Please upload at least one audio file (60+ seconds total recommended).",
                variant: "destructive"
            });
            return
        }
        M.mutate({
            name: s,
            description: l.trim() || void 0,
            audioFiles: u
        })
    }

                audio: !0
            })
              , F = new MediaRecorder(Z);
            T.current = F,
            L.current = [],
            F.ondataavailable = Y => {
                Y.data.size > 0 && L.current.push(Y.data)
            }
            ,
            F.onstop = () => {
                const Y = new Blob(L.current,{
                    type: "audio/webm"
                })
                  , W = URL.createObjectURL(Y);
                S(W);
                const ee = new FileReader;
                ee.onloadend = () => {
                    const se = ee.result;
                    f([se])
                }
                ,
                ee.readAsDataURL(Y),
                Z.getTracks().forEach(se => se.stop()),
                R.current && clearInterval(R.current)
            }
            ,
            F.start(),
            v(!0),
            b(!1),
            x(0),
            R.current = window.setInterval( () => {
                x(Y => Y + 1)
            }
            , 1e3)
        } catch {
            e({
                title: "Recording Failed",
                description: "Unable to access microphone. Please check permissions.",
                variant: "destructive"
            })
        }
    }
      , ne = () => {
        T.current && T.current.state === "recording" && (T.current.pause(),
        b(!0),
        R.current && clearInterval(R.current))
    }
      , fe = () => {
        T.current && T.current.state === "paused" && (T.current.resume(),
        b(!1),
        R.current = window.setInterval( () => {
            x(Z => Z + 1)
        }
        , 1e3))
    }
      , ue = () => {
        T.current && (T.current.stop(),
        v(!1),
        b(!1))
    }
      , oe = () => {
        (g || m) && ue(),

        f([]),
        L.current = []
    }
      , le = () => {
        if (w) {
            const Z = new Audio(w);
            B.current = Z,
            Z.play(),
            C(!0),
            Z.onended = () => C(!1)
        }
    }
      , ie = () => {
        B.current && (B.current.pause(),
        C(!1))
    }
      , de = Z => {
        const F = Math.floor(Z / 60)
          , Y = Z % 60;
        return `${F}:${Y.toString().padStart(2, "0")}`
    }
    ;
    return p.useEffect( () => () => {
        R.current && clearInterval(R.current),
        B.current && B.current.pause()
    }
    , []),

        })]
    })

                                className: "text-sm text-destructive",
                                children: T.errorMessage || "Generation failed"
                            })]
                        })]
                    }, T.id))
                })
            })]
        })]
    })
}

    key: "audio-wav-conversion",

      , {getModelCost: t} = Ni()

      , j = T => {

            });

        }

                title: "File Too Large",

        }

            var M;

            })

                variant: "destructive"
            })
        }
        ,

    }

        if (!r) {

                title: "Validation Error",

        }

                                    src: T.resultUrl,
                                    controls: !0,
                                    className: "w-full",
                                    "data-testid": `audio-${T.id}`
                                })
                            })]
                        }, T.id)
                    }
                    )
                })
            })]
        })]
    })
}

                        }()
                          , P = 63;
                        return function(N) {

                    this._instanceId = S.instanceCount++,
                    this._options = P
                }
                get width() {
                    return this._options.width
                }
                get height() {
                    return this._options.height
                }
                getElement() {
                    return this._element
                }
                async drawQR(P) {
                    const N = P.getModuleCount()
                      , k = Math.min(this._options.width, this._options.height) - 2 * this._options.margin
                      , $ = this._options.shape === y ? k / Math.sqrt(2) : k
                      , D = this._roundSize($ / N);
                    let U = {
                        hideXDots: 0,
                        hideYDots: 0,
                        width: 0,
                        height: 0
                    };
                    if (this._qr = P,
                    this._options.image) {
                        if (await this.loadImage(),
                        !this._image)
                            return;
                        const {imageOptions: Q, qrOptions: ne} = this._options
                          , fe = Q.imageSize * u[ne.errorCorrectionLevel]
                          , ue = Math.floor(fe * N * N);
                        U = function({originalHeight: oe, originalWidth: le, maxHiddenDots: ie, maxHiddenAxisDots: de, dotSize: Z}) {
                            const F = {
                                x: 0,
                                y: 0
                            }
                              , Y = {
                                x: 0,
                                y: 0
                            };
                            if (oe <= 0 || le <= 0 || ie <= 0 || Z <= 0)
                                return {
                                    height: 0,
                                    width: 0,
                                    hideYDots: 0,
                                    hideXDots: 0
                                };
                            const W = oe / le;
                            return F.x = Math.floor(Math.sqrt(ie / W)),
                            F.x <= 0 && (F.x = 1),
                            de && de < F.x && (F.x = de),
                            F.x % 2 == 0 && F.x--,
                            Y.x = F.x * Z,
                            F.y = 1 + 2 * Math.ceil((F.x * W - 1) / 2),
                            Y.y = Math.round(Y.x * W),
                            (F.y * F.x > ie || de && de < F.y) && (de && de < F.y ? (F.y = de,
                            F.y % 2 == 0 && F.x--) : F.y -= 2,
                            Y.y = F.y * Z,
                            F.x = 1 + 2 * Math.ceil((F.y / W - 1) / 2),
                            Y.x = Math.round(Y.y / W)),
                            {
                                height: Y.y,
                                width: Y.x,
                                hideYDots: F.y,
                                hideXDots: F.x
                            }
                        }({
                            originalWidth: this._image.width,
                            originalHeight: this._image.height,
                            maxHiddenDots: ue,
                            maxHiddenAxisDots: N - 14,
                            dotSize: D
                        })
                    }
                    this.drawBackground(),
                    this.drawDots( (Q, ne) => {
                        var fe, ue, oe, le, ie, de;
                        return !(this._options.imageOptions.hideBackgroundDots && Q >= (N - U.hideYDots) / 2 && Q < (N + U.hideYDots) / 2 && ne >= (N - U.hideXDots) / 2 && ne < (N + U.hideXDots) / 2 || !((fe = x[Q]) === null || fe === void 0) && fe[ne] || !((ue = x[Q - N + 7]) === null || ue === void 0) && ue[ne] || !((oe = x[Q]) === null || oe === void 0) && oe[ne - N + 7] || !((le = w[Q]) === null || le === void 0) && le[ne] || !((ie = w[Q - N + 7]) === null || ie === void 0) && ie[ne] || !((de = w[Q]) === null || de === void 0) && de[ne - N + 7])
                    }
                    ),
                    this.drawCorners(),
                    this._options.image && await this.drawImage({
                        width: U.width,
                        height: U.height,
                        count: N,
                        dotSize: D
                    })
                }
                drawBackground() {
                    var P, N, k;
                    const $ = this._element
                      , D = this._options;
                    if ($) {
                        const U = (P = D.backgroundOptions) === null || P === void 0 ? void 0 : P.gradient
                          , Q = (N = D.backgroundOptions) === null || N === void 0 ? void 0 : N.color;
                        let ne = D.height
                          , fe = D.width;
                        if (U || Q) {
                            const ue = this._window.document.createElementNS("http://www.w3.org/2000/svg", "rect");

                                options: U,

                                x: 0,
                                y: 0,

                    }
                }
                drawDots(P) {
                    var N, k;

                        throw "QR code is not defined";
                    const $ = this._options
                      , D = this._qr.getModuleCount();
                    if (D > $.width || D > $.height)
                        throw "The canvas is too small.";

                    });

                            P && !P(le, ie) || !((k = this._qr) === null || k === void 0) && k.isDark(le, ie) && (oe.draw(fe + ie * ne, ue + le * ne, ne, (de, Z) => !(ie + de < 0 || le + Z < 0 || ie + de >= D || le + Z >= D) && !(P && !P(le + Z, ie + de)) && !!this._qr && this._qr.isDark(le + Z, ie + de)),

                    }
                }

                loadImage() {
                    return new Promise( (P, N) => {
                        var k;
                        const $ = this._options;
                        if (!$.image)
                            return N("Image is not defined");

                            ).catch(N);

                            this._image = D,
                            D.onload = async () => {
                                this._options.imageOptions.saveAsBlob && (this._imageUri = await async function(U, Q) {

                                        const fe = new Q.XMLHttpRequest;
                                        fe.onload = function() {
                                            const ue = new Q.FileReader;
                                            ue.onloadend = function() {
                                                ne(ue.result)
                                            }
                                            ,
                                            ue.readAsDataURL(fe.response)
                                        }
                                        ,
                                        fe.open("GET", U),
                                        fe.responseType = "blob",
                                        fe.send()
                                    }
                                    )
                                }($.image || "", this._window)),
                                P()
                            }
                            ,

                        }

                    )

                async drawImage({width: P, height: N, count: k, dotSize: $}) {
                    const D = this._options
                      , U = this._roundSize((D.width - k * $) / 2)
                      , Q = this._roundSize((D.height - k * $) / 2)
                      , ne = U + this._roundSize(D.imageOptions.margin + (k * $ - P) / 2)
                      , fe = Q + this._roundSize(D.imageOptions.margin + (k * $ - N) / 2)
                      , ue = P - 2 * D.imageOptions.margin
                      , oe = N - 2 * D.imageOptions.margin
                      , le = this._window.document.createElementNS("http://www.w3.org/2000/svg", "image");
                    le.setAttribute("href", this._imageUri || ""),
                    le.setAttribute("xlink:href", this._imageUri || ""),
                    le.setAttribute("x", String(ne)),
                    le.setAttribute("y", String(fe)),
                    le.setAttribute("width", `${ue}px`),
                    le.setAttribute("height", `${oe}px`),
                    this._element.appendChild(le)
                }
                _createColor({options: P, color: N, additionalRotation: k, x: $, y: D, height: U, width: Q, name: ne}) {
                    const fe = Q > U ? Q : U
                      , ue = this._window.document.createElementNS("http://www.w3.org/2000/svg", "rect");
                    if (ue.setAttribute("x", String($)),
                    ue.setAttribute("y", String(D)),
                    ue.setAttribute("height", String(U)),
                    ue.setAttribute("width", String(Q)),
                    ue.setAttribute("clip-path", `url('#clip-path-${ne}')`),
                    P) {
                        let oe;
                        if (P.type === "radial")
                            oe = this._window.document.createElementNS("http://www.w3.org/2000/svg", "radialGradient"),
                            oe.setAttribute("id", ne),
                            oe.setAttribute("gradientUnits", "userSpaceOnUse"),
                            oe.setAttribute("fx", String($ + Q / 2)),
                            oe.setAttribute("fy", String(D + U / 2)),
                            oe.setAttribute("cx", String($ + Q / 2)),
                            oe.setAttribute("cy", String(D + U / 2)),
                            oe.setAttribute("r", String(fe / 2));
                        else {
                            const le = ((P.rotation || 0) + k) % (2 * Math.PI)
                              , ie = (le + 2 * Math.PI) % (2 * Math.PI);
                            let de = $ + Q / 2
                              , Z = D + U / 2
                              , F = $ + Q / 2
                              , Y = D + U / 2;
                            ie >= 0 && ie <= .25 * Math.PI || ie > 1.75 * Math.PI && ie <= 2 * Math.PI ? (de -= Q / 2,
                            Z -= U / 2 * Math.tan(le),
                            F += Q / 2,
                            Y += U / 2 * Math.tan(le)) : ie > .25 * Math.PI && ie <= .75 * Math.PI ? (Z -= U / 2,
                            de -= Q / 2 / Math.tan(le),
                            Y += U / 2,
                            F += Q / 2 / Math.tan(le)) : ie > .75 * Math.PI && ie <= 1.25 * Math.PI ? (de += Q / 2,
                            Z += U / 2 * Math.tan(le),
                            F -= Q / 2,
                            Y -= U / 2 * Math.tan(le)) : ie > 1.25 * Math.PI && ie <= 1.75 * Math.PI && (Z += U / 2,
                            de += Q / 2 / Math.tan(le),
                            Y -= U / 2,
                            F -= Q / 2 / Math.tan(le)),
                            oe = this._window.document.createElementNS("http://www.w3.org/2000/svg", "linearGradient"),
                            oe.setAttribute("id", ne),
                            oe.setAttribute("gradientUnits", "userSpaceOnUse"),
                            oe.setAttribute("x1", String(Math.round(de))),
                            oe.setAttribute("y1", String(Math.round(Z))),
                            oe.setAttribute("x2", String(Math.round(F))),
                            oe.setAttribute("y2", String(Math.round(Y)))
                        }
                        P.colorStops.forEach( ({offset: le, color: ie}) => {
                            const de = this._window.document.createElementNS("http://www.w3.org/2000/svg", "stop");
                            de.setAttribute("offset", 100 * le + "%"),
                            de.setAttribute("stop-color", ie),
                            oe.appendChild(de)
                        }
                        ),
                        ue.setAttribute("fill", `url('#${ne}')`),
                        this._defs.appendChild(oe)
                    } else
                        N && ue.setAttribute("fill", N);
                    this._element.appendChild(ue)
                }
            }
            S.instanceCount = 0;

            function T(M) {
                const P = Object.assign({}, M);
                if (!P.colorStops || !P.colorStops.length)
                    throw "Field 'colorStops' is required in gradient";
                return P.rotation ? P.rotation = Number(P.rotation) : P.rotation = 0,
                P.colorStops = P.colorStops.map(N => Object.assign(Object.assign({}, N), {
                    offset: Number(N.offset)
                })),
                P
            }
            function L(M) {
                const P = Object.assign({}, M);
                return P.width = Number(P.width),
                P.height = Number(P.height),
                P.margin = Number(P.margin),
                P.imageOptions = Object.assign(Object.assign({}, P.imageOptions), {
                    hideBackgroundDots: !!P.imageOptions.hideBackgroundDots,
                    imageSize: Number(P.imageOptions.imageSize),
                    margin: Number(P.imageOptions.margin)
                }),
                P.margin > Math.min(P.width, P.height) && (P.margin = Math.min(P.width, P.height)),
                P.dotsOptions = Object.assign({}, P.dotsOptions),
                P.dotsOptions.gradient && (P.dotsOptions.gradient = T(P.dotsOptions.gradient)),
                P.cornersSquareOptions && (P.cornersSquareOptions = Object.assign({}, P.cornersSquareOptions),

                P.cornersDotOptions.gradient && (P.cornersDotOptions.gradient = T(P.cornersDotOptions.gradient))),
                P.backgroundOptions && (P.backgroundOptions = Object.assign({}, P.backgroundOptions),
                P.backgroundOptions.gradient && (P.backgroundOptions.gradient = T(P.backgroundOptions.gradient))),
                P
            }
            var R = a(873)
              , B = a.n(R);
            function I(M) {
                if (!M)
                    throw new Error("Extension must be defined");
                M[0] === "." && (M = M.substring(1));
                const P = {
                    bmp: "image/bmp",
                    gif: "image/gif",
                    ico: "image/vnd.microsoft.icon",
                    jpeg: "image/jpeg",
                    jpg: "image/jpeg",
                    png: "image/png",
                    svg: "image/svg+xml",
                    tif: "image/tiff",
                    tiff: "image/tiff",
                    webp: "image/webp",
                    pdf: "application/pdf"
                }[M.toLowerCase()];
                if (!P)
                    throw new Error(`Extension "${M}" is not supported`);
                return P
            }
            class A {
                constructor(P) {
                    P != null && P.jsdom ? this._window = new P.jsdom("",{

                    }).window : this._window = window,

                static _clearContainer(P) {
                    P && (P.innerHTML = "")
                }
                _setupSvg() {

                }
                _setupCanvas() {
                    var P, N;
                    this._qr && (!((P = this._options.nodeCanvas) === null || P === void 0) && P.createCanvas ? (this._nodeCanvas = this._options.nodeCanvas.createCanvas(this._options.width, this._options.height),
                    this._nodeCanvas.width = this._options.width,
                    this._nodeCanvas.height = this._options.height) : (this._domCanvas = document.createElement("canvas"),
                    this._domCanvas.width = this._options.width,
                    this._domCanvas.height = this._options.height),
                    this._setupSvg(),
                    this._canvasDrawingPromise = (N = this._svgDrawingPromise) === null || N === void 0 ? void 0 : N.then( () => {
                        var k;
                        if (!this._svg)
                            return;
                        const $ = this._svg
                          , D = new this._window.XMLSerializer().serializeToString($)
                          , U = btoa(D)
                          , Q = `data:${I("svg")};base64,${U}`;
                        if (!((k = this._options.nodeCanvas) === null || k === void 0) && k.loadImage)
                            return this._options.nodeCanvas.loadImage(Q).then(ne => {
                                var fe, ue;
                                ne.width = this._options.width,
                                ne.height = this._options.height,
                                (ue = (fe = this._nodeCanvas) === null || fe === void 0 ? void 0 : fe.getContext("2d")) === null || ue === void 0 || ue.drawImage(ne, 0, 0)
                            }
                            );
                        {
