                            return new Promise(fe => {
                                ne.onload = () => {
                                    var ue, oe;
                                    (oe = (ue = this._domCanvas) === null || ue === void 0 ? void 0 : ue.getContext("2d")) === null || oe === void 0 || oe.drawImage(ne, 0, 0),
                                    fe()
                                }
                                ,
                                ne.src = Q
                            }
                            )
                        }
                    }
                    ))
                }
                async _getElement(P="png") {
                    if (!this._qr)
                        throw "QR code is empty";
                    return P.toLowerCase() === "svg" ? (this._svg && this._svgDrawingPromise || this._setupSvg(),
                    await this._svgDrawingPromise,
                    this._svg) : ((this._domCanvas || this._nodeCanvas) && this._canvasDrawingPromise || this._setupCanvas(),
                    await this._canvasDrawingPromise,
                    this._domCanvas || this._nodeCanvas)
                }
                update(P) {
                    A._clearContainer(this._container),
                    this._options = P ? L(l(this._options, P)) : this._options,
                    this._options.data && (this._qr = B()(this._options.qrOptions.typeNumber, this._options.qrOptions.errorCorrectionLevel),
                    this._qr.addData(this._options.data, this._options.qrOptions.mode || function(N) {
                        switch (!0) {
                        case /^[0-9]*$/.test(N):
                            return "Numeric";
                        case /^[0-9A-Z $%*+\-./:]*$/.test(N):
                            return "Alphanumeric";
                        default:
                            return "Byte"
                        }
                    }(this._options.data)),
                    this._qr.make(),
                    this._options.type === C ? this._setupCanvas() : this._setupSvg(),
                    this.append(this._container))
                }
                append(P) {
                    if (P) {
                        if (typeof P.appendChild != "function")
                            throw "Container should be a single DOM node";
                        this._options.type === C ? this._domCanvas && P.appendChild(this._domCanvas) : this._svg && P.appendChild(this._svg),
                        this._container = P
                    }
                }
                applyExtension(P) {
                    if (!P)
                        throw "Extension function should be defined.";
                    this._extension = P,
                    this.update()
                }
                deleteExtension() {
                    this._extension = void 0,
                    this.update()
                }
                async getRawData(P="png") {
                    if (!this._qr)
                        throw "QR code is empty";
                    const N = await this._getElement(P)
                      , k = I(P);
                    if (!N)
                        return null;
                    if (P.toLowerCase() === "svg") {
                        const $ = `<?xml version="1.0" standalone="no"?>\r
${new this._window.XMLSerializer().serializeToString(N)}`;
                        return typeof Blob > "u" || this._options.jsdom ? Buffer.from($) : new Blob([$],{
                            type: k
                        })
                    }
                    return new Promise($ => {
                        const D = N;
                        if ("toBuffer"in D)
                            if (k === "image/png")
                                $(D.toBuffer(k));
                            else if (k === "image/jpeg")
                                $(D.toBuffer(k));
                            else {
                                if (k !== "application/pdf")
                                    throw Error("Unsupported extension");
                                $(D.toBuffer(k))
                            }
                        else
                            "toBlob"in D && D.toBlob($, k, 1)
                    }
                    )
                }
                async download(P) {
                    if (!this._qr)
                        throw "QR code is empty";
                    if (typeof Blob > "u")
                        throw "Cannot download in Node.js, call getRawData instead.";
                    let N = "png"
                      , k = "qr";
                    typeof P == "string" ? (N = P,
                    console.warn("Extension is deprecated as argument for 'download' method, please pass object { name: '...', extension: '...' } as argument")) : typeof P == "object" && P !== null && (P.name && (k = P.name),
                    P.extension && (N = P.extension));
                    const $ = await this._getElement(N);
                    if ($)
                        if (N.toLowerCase() === "svg") {
                            let D = new XMLSerializer().serializeToString($);
                            D = `<?xml version="1.0" standalone="no"?>\r
` + D,
                            c(`data:${I(N)};charset=utf-8,${encodeURIComponent(D)}`, `${k}.svg`)
                        } else
                            c($.toDataURL(I(N)), `${k}.${N}`)
                }
            }
            const E = A
        }
        )(),
        s.default
    }
    )())
}

    deepseek: [{
        value: "deepseek-chat",
        label: "Deepseek Chat"
    }],

        value: "gpt-4o",
        label: "GPT-4o"

function cX() {
    var L;
    const {toast: e} = ft()
      , {getModelCost: t} = Ni()
      , [r,n] = p.useState(null)
      , [a,s] = p.useState("deepseek")
      , [o,l] = p.useState("deepseek-chat")
      , [c,u] = p.useState("")
      , [f,d] = p.useState("")
      , [h,g] = p.useState(!1)
      , [v,m] = p.useState("")
      , b = p.useRef(null)
      , y = p.useRef(null)
      , x = p.useMemo( () => ({
        deepseek: LA.deepseek.map(R => ({
            ...R,
            cost: t(R.value, 5)
        })),
        openai: LA.openai.map(R => ({
            ...R,
            cost: t(R.value, 10)
        }))
    }), [t])
      , {data: w=[]} = Qe({
        queryKey: ["/api/chat/conversations"]
    })
      , {data: S=[]} = Qe({
        queryKey: ["/api/chat/conversations", r],
        enabled: !!r
    })
      , j = Ge({
        mutationFn: async R => {
            await Le("DELETE", `/api/chat/conversations/${R}`)
        }
        ,
        onSuccess: () => {
            tt.invalidateQueries({
                queryKey: ["/api/chat/conversations"]
            }),
            n(null),
            e({
                title: "Conversation deleted",
                description: "The conversation has been removed."
            })
        }
    });
    p.useEffect( () => {
        var R;
        (R = b.current) == null || R.scrollIntoView({
            behavior: "smooth"
        })
    }
    , [S, f]),
    p.useEffect( () => {
        const R = x[a];
        R.length > 0 && l(R[0].value)
    }
    , [a]);
    const C = () => {
        y.current && (y.current.abort(),
        y.current = null,
        g(!1),
        d(""),
        m(""),
        e({
            title: "Stopped",
            description: "Response generation stopped"
        }))
    }
      , O = async () => {
        var B;
        if (!c.trim())
            return;
        const R = c;
        u(""),
        g(!0),
        d(""),
        m(R);
        try {
            const I = new AbortController;
            y.current = I;
            const A = {
                message: R,
                provider: a,
                model: o
            };
            r && (A.conversationId = r);
            const E = await Kd("/api/chat/send", {
                method: "POST",
                headers: {
                    "Content-Type": "application/json"
                },
                body: JSON.stringify(A),
                signal: I.signal,
                credentials: "include"
            });
            if (!E.ok)
                throw new Error("Failed to send message");
            const M = (B = E.body) == null ? void 0 : B.getReader()
              , P = new TextDecoder;
            if (!M)
                throw new Error("No response body");
            let N = "";
            for (; ; ) {
                const {done: k, value: $} = await M.read();
                if (k)
                    break;
                N += P.decode($, {
                    stream: !0
                });
                const D = N.split(`
`);
                N = D.pop() || "";
                for (const U of D)
                    if (U.startsWith("data: ")) {
                        const Q = JSON.parse(U.slice(6));
                        if (Q.error)
                            throw new Error(Q.error);
                        if (Q.done) {
                            g(!1),
                            m(""),
                            y.current = null;
                            const ne = Q.conversationId || r;
                            Q.conversationId && !r && n(Q.conversationId),
                            await Promise.all([tt.invalidateQueries({
                                queryKey: ["/api/chat/conversations"]
                            }), tt.invalidateQueries({
                                queryKey: ["/api/chat/conversations", ne]
                            }), tt.invalidateQueries({
                                queryKey: ["/api/auth/user"]
                            })]),
                            setTimeout( () => {
                                d("")
                            }
                            , 100)
                        } else
                            d(ne => ne + Q.content)
                    }
            }
        } catch (I) {
            I.name === "AbortError" || y.current === null || (console.error("Chat error:", I),
            e({
                title: "Error",
                description: I.message || "Failed to send message",
                variant: "destructive"
            })),
            g(!1),
            d(""),
            m(""),
            y.current = null
        }
    }
      , _ = () => {
        n(null),
        u(""),
        d(""),
        m("")
    }
      , T = ((L = x[a].find(R => R.value === o)) == null ? void 0 : L.cost) || 10;
    return i.jsxs("div", {
        className: "flex h-full",
        children: [i.jsxs("div", {
            className: "w-80 border-r bg-card flex flex-col",
            children: [i.jsx("div", {
                className: "p-4 border-b",
                children: i.jsxs(G, {
                    "data-testid": "button-new-chat",
                    onClick: _,
                    className: "w-full",
                    variant: "default",
                    children: [i.jsx(_i, {
                        className: "w-4 h-4 mr-2"
                    }), "New Chat"]

function NX({generation: e}) {
    const {toast: t} = ft()
      , [,r] = Yo()
      , [n,a] = p.useState(!1)
      , [s,o] = p.useState(!1)
      , [l,c] = p.useState(!1)
      , [u,f] = p.useState(!1)
      , d = {
        pending: "secondary",
        processing: "default",
        completed: "default",
        failed: "destructive"
    }
      , h = Ge({
        mutationFn: async () => await Le("DELETE", `/api/generations/${e.id}`),
        onSuccess: () => {
            t({
                title: "Success",
                description: "Generation deleted successfully"
            }),
            tt.invalidateQueries({
                queryKey: ["/api/generations"]
            })
        }
        ,
        onError: j => {
            t({
                title: "Error",
                description: j.message || "Failed to delete generation",
                variant: "destructive"
            })
        }
    })
      , g = async () => {
        if (e.resultUrl)
            try {
                const j = await Kd(`/api/generations/${e.id}/download`, {
                    credentials: "include"
                });
                if (!j.ok)
                    throw new Error("Download failed");
                const C = await j.blob()
                  , O = window.URL.createObjectURL(C)
                  , _ = document.createElement("a");
                _.href = O;
                const T = j.headers.get("Content-Disposition")
                  , L = T == null ? void 0 : T.match(/filename="(.+)"/);
                _.download = (L == null ? void 0 : L[1]) || `artivio-${e.type}-${e.id}`,
                document.body.appendChild(_),
                _.click(),
                window.URL.revokeObjectURL(O),
                document.body.removeChild(_),
                t({
                    title: "Download started",
                    description: "Your file is being downloaded"
                })
            } catch (j) {
                if (console.error("Download failed:", j),
                j instanceof Error && j.message === "SESSION_EXPIRED") {
                    t({
                        title: "Session expired",
                        description: "Please log in again to continue",
                        variant: "destructive"
                    }),
                    setTimeout( () => window.location.href = "/login", 1500);
                    return
                }
                t({
                    title: "Download failed",
                    description: j instanceof Error ? j.message : "Could not download the file. Please try again.",
                    variant: "destructive"
                })
            }
    }
      , v = () => {
        h.mutate(),
        c(!1)
    }
      , m = () => {
        navigator.clipboard.writeText(e.prompt),
        t({
            title: "Copied",
            description: "Prompt copied to clipboard"
        })
    }
      , b = {
        video: "/generate/video",
        image: "/generate/image",
        music: "/generate/music"
    }
      , y = e.type in b
      , x = () => {
        const j = b[e.type];
        j && (sessionStorage.setItem("regeneratePrompt", e.prompt),
        sessionStorage.setItem("regenerateModel", e.model),
        r(j))
    }
      , w = () => {
        e.type === "video" && e.resultUrl && a(!0)

class yre {
    constructor(t) {
        this._x0 = this._y0 = this._x1 = this._y1 = null,
        this._ = "",
        this._append = t == null ? gD : xre(t)
    }
    moveTo(t, r) {
        this._append`M${this._x0 = this._x1 = +t},${this._y0 = this._y1 = +r}`
    }
    closePath() {
        this._x1 !== null && (this._x1 = this._x0,
        this._y1 = this._y0,
        this._append`Z`)
    }
    lineTo(t, r) {
        this._append`L${this._x1 = +t},${this._y1 = +r}`
    }
    quadraticCurveTo(t, r, n, a) {
        this._append`Q${+t},${+r},${this._x1 = +n},${this._y1 = +a}`
    }
    bezierCurveTo(t, r, n, a, s, o) {
        this._append`C${+t},${+r},${+n},${+a},${this._x1 = +s},${this._y1 = +o}`
    }
    arcTo(t, r, n, a, s) {
        if (t = +t,
        r = +r,
        n = +n,
        a = +a,
        s = +s,
        s < 0)
            throw new Error(`negative radius: ${s}`);
        let o = this._x1
          , l = this._y1
          , c = n - t
          , u = a - r
          , f = o - t
          , d = l - r
          , h = f * f + d * d;
        if (this._x1 === null)
            this._append`M${this._x1 = t},${this._y1 = r}`;
        else if (h > eo)
            if (!(Math.abs(d * c - u * f) > eo) || !s)
                this._append`L${this._x1 = t},${this._y1 = r}`;
            else {
                let g = n - o
                  , v = a - l
                  , m = c * c + u * u
                  , b = g * g + v * v
                  , y = Math.sqrt(m)
                  , x = Math.sqrt(h)
                  , w = s * Math.tan((fw - Math.acos((m + h - b) / (2 * y * x))) / 2)
                  , S = w / x
                  , j = w / y;

            }
    }

        r = +r,
        n = +n,
        o = !!o,
        n < 0)
            throw new Error(`negative radius: ${n}`);
        let l = n * Math.cos(a)
          , c = n * Math.sin(a)
          , u = t + l
          , f = r + c
          , d = 1 ^ o
          , h = o ? a - s : s - a;

        n && (h < 0 && (h = h % hw + hw),

    }

    }
}

function sP(e) {

    s[0] = 2,
    o[0] = e[0] + 2 * e[1],
    t = 1; t < r - 1; ++t)

        o[t] = 4 * e[t] + 2 * e[t + 1];

    s[r - 1] = 7,

        var n = r.call(e, t || "default");
        if (Qc(n) != "object")
            return n;
        throw new TypeError("@@toPrimitive must return a primitive value.")
    }

}

                            if (!be.message.trim()) {
                                e({
                                    title: "Error",

                                });
                                return
                            }
                            try {

                                    isActive: be.isActive,

                                    endDate: be.endDate || null
                                };
                                ve ? await Le("PATCH", `/api/admin/announcements/${ve}`, z) : await Le("POST", "/api/admin/announcements", z),

                                    queryKey: ["/api/admin/announcements"]
                                }),
                                a.invalidateQueries({
                                    queryKey: ["/api/announcements/active"]
                                }),
                                se(!1),

                                    title: "Success",
                                    description: `Announcement ${ve ? "updated" : "created"} successfully`
                                })
                            } catch (z) {
                                e({
                                    title: "Error",
                                    description: z.message || `Failed to ${ve ? "update" : "create"} announcement`,
                                    variant: "destructive"
                                })
                            }
                        }
                        ,
                        "data-testid": "button-save-announcement",
                        children: ve ? "Update" : "Create"
                    })]
                })]
            })
        })]
    })
}

                            })
                        })]

                })
            })]
        })]
    })
}
function wNe() {

    })
      , r = a => {
        switch (a) {
        case 0:

                className: "h-6 w-6 text-yellow-500"
            });

            });

            });

            })
        }
    }
      , n = a => {
        const s = a.split(" ").filter(o => o);

    }
    ;

function SNe() {
    const {isAuthenticated: e, isLoading: t} = nr()
      , [r,n] = Yo();
    return p.useEffect( () => {
        const a = new URLSearchParams(window.location.search);
        if (a.get("logout") === "success") {
            console.log("[AUTH] Logout detected - clearing all cached data"),
            tt.clear(),
            a.delete("logout");
            const s = a.toString()
              , o = window.location.pathname + (s ? `?${s}` : "");
            window.history.replaceState({}, "", o),
            console.log("[AUTH]  Cache cleared and URL cleaned")
        }
    }
    , [r]),
    t ? i.jsx("div", {
        className: "flex items-center justify-center h-screen",
